132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 611
H.P. 379 House of Representatives, February 25, 2025
An Act to Allow the Secretary of State to Collect Excise Taxes on
Motor Vehicles Owned by Residents Who Are Unhoused
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Transportation pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SAYRE of Kennebunk.
Cosponsored by Senator RAFFERTY of York and
Representatives: CRAFTS of Newcastle, JULIA of Waterville, KUHN of Falmouth, LEE of
Auburn, MOONEN of Portland, RANA of Bangor, SATO of Gorham.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1484, sub-§3, ¶A, as amended by PL 2007, c. 627, §33, is
3 further amended to read:
4 A. The excise tax on a motor vehicle owned by an individual resident of this State
5 must be paid in the place where the owner resides. If the individual resident of this
6 State has no residing place, the excise tax may be paid directly to the Secretary of State.
7 SUMMARY
88 This bill allows an individual resident of the State who has no residing place to pay
99 excise tax on a motor vehicle directly to the Secretary of State.
